      <bioghist id="aspace_c1a8f9e727c630e92be1ed8d1fba7e40">
         <head>Biographical / Historical</head>
         <p>The Berkeley Association (1869-1955), an Episcopalian student organization, was founded at Yale to promote Christianity according to tenets of the Episcopal Church.</p>  
      </bioghist>
      <scopecontent id="aspace_5171978d1673ed99eae32b6ca72d90f7">
         <head>Scope and Contents</head>
         <p>The records consist of minutes, general files, a constitution, and membership lists documenting the operations of the Yale Berkeley Association.</p>  
      </scopecontent>
